From vscode-dotnettools created by [brandonryan](https://github.com/brandonryan): microsoft/vscode-dotnettools#302  

### Describe the Issue

`dotnet.completion.showCompletionItemsFromUnimportedNamespaces` is enabled.
When I write a custom extension for classes, the auto completion does not provide it as an option.

### Steps To Reproduce

`Extensions/DateExtensions.cs`
```csharp
using System;

namespace Brandon.Expirements.Extensions
{
    public static class DateExtensions
    {
        public static void Test(this DateOnly d)
        {
            
        }
    }
}
```

`Program.cs`
```csharp
using System;

namespace Brandon.Expirements
{
    public static class Program
    {
        public static void Main()
        {
            var d = new DateOnly();
            d. //auto complete should complete DateExtensions Test method but does not.
        }
    }    
}

```


### Expected Behavior

`Test()` would be provided as an import option.

### Environment Information

OS: Windows 11
VS Code Version: 1.80.2
ExtensionVersion: 0.2.100 (i think)

